cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CC 

This paper is about Natural Language Processing (NLP) and focuses on modeling the explanation regeneration task as a learning to rank problem. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses state-of-the-art language models, which suggests the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as a likely option. Additionally, the iterative re-ranking approach used in the paper is a common technique in machine learning, which could place the paper in the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with multi-hop inference on large graphs, which could suggest the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
